article.description: Nathan Knight had 15 points and 11 rebounds as William & Mary beat Division III Goucher 90-30 on Sunday.
article.headline: Knight carries William & Mary past Goucher 90-30
article.linkText: Knight carries William & Mary past Goucher 90-30
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. -- Nathan Knight had 15 points and 11 rebounds as William & Mary beat Division III Goucher 90-30 on Sunday. Andy Van Vliet added 11 points and 13 rebounds for the Tribe. Jihar Williams had 10 points for William & Mary (8-3), which earned its fourth straight home victory. Mehkel Harvey added 10 rebounds. William & Mary posted a season-high 66 rebounds. Meanwhile, the Gophers' 30 points on 22.4 percent shooting represented the worst marks by a William & Mary opponent this season. Additionally, the Tribe swatted a season-high 10 blocks. Dwayne Morton had 10 points for the Gophers. William & Mary faces Saint Joseph's on the road on Thursday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
